Ordering a lot from this place lately, food is great but today i was disappointed when i got a small dry piece of chicken leg while it says on the menu HALF ROASTED CHICKEN (16$) The portion of that meal should not cost more than 10$.

Cute romantic Mediterranean restaurant located few blocks from my apartment. It's been under construction for some time and they finally open! Came with my girlfriends on a Thursday night and let me tell you we thoroughly enjoyed our drinks, deserts, hookah and more! First off, there was a dj spinning on a Thursday night with really good music, it wasnt those obnoxious loud club songs so we were able to still have conversation and hear each other. The deCor was very romantic and elegant with a large gold mirror at the bar and hanging light fixtures, the red wall lighting made it very romantic. Service was quick and we love our waitress she was very attentive! We had dinner prior to this so we only tried deserts and drinks! Definitely try the strawberry cheese cakes and baklava they were super tasty reminds me of those homemade ones. The hookah was very flavor full we had the strawberry banana and it lasted super long since we were there until midnight enjoying the music. This is truly a gem of a place with great ambiance and laid back vibe. Cant wait to come back this weekend and try more of there food plus our waitress said there's Dj's on the weekends too! Found my new spot in Bk that has manhattan vibes but without actually going to the city for over price food and drinks! I highly recommend!!

Shady pricing. Ordered linguini over the phone and the person said one price that matches price on their website, but 15 min later was charged $7 extra due to lame explanation of their “dinner” pricing. I definitely do not recommend this place.  Update: I indeed got a refund in full. However I didn’t like that at first when I addressed this issue, the barmen just shrugged his shoulder without even trying to solve this issue in the first place. That’s when I wrote this review. While I was sharing my experience with deli store next door to this place, I’ve been advised to go back to return the order and request a full refund. Only upon my return and determination to get a refund, I was approached by someone in charge. I was not told at that time that I’m being refunded in full, in fact that person just told me that he refunded a difference in “I’m so annoyed” tone. There were no apologies whatsoever. The food is decent there, but the lack of customer service and different pricing in their menu vs website vs daytime vs nighttime is too much for my liking, thus I still do not recommend this place. However I’ll add 2 more stars to my review due to being refunded in full and decent meal.
